{{infobox football tournament season | title = South Sudan National Cup | year = 2018 | other_title = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | country = {{SSD}} | num_teams = | champions = [[Al Merreikh FC (South Sudan)|Al-Merreikh Juba]] | runner-up = | matches = | goals = | top goal scorer = | player = | prevseason = [[2017 South Sudan National Cup|2017]] | nextseason = [[2019 South Sudan National Cup|2019]] }}
The '''2018 South Sudan National Cup''' is the 6th edition of the [[South Sudan National Cup]], the knockout [[association football|football]] competition of [[South Sudan]].
==Group stage== There were two groups, with Group A played in [[Juba]] and Group B played in [[Aweil, South Sudan|Aweil]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesz/zsoed2018.html#cup South Sudan Cup 2018], RSSSF.com</ref>
[[Al Merreikh FC (South Sudan)|Al-Merreikh]] won Group A and [[Al Ghazala FC|Al-Ghazala]] won Group B.
==Final== The final was played on 14 August 2018 at the [[Juba Stadium]] in [[Juba]].
[[Al Merreikh FC (South Sudan)|Al-Merreikh Juba]] 2–0 [[Al Ghazala FC|Al-Ghazala]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hotinjuba.com/merikh-fc-crowned-south-sudan-cup-champions-bags-ssp-500000/|title=Merikh FC crowned South Sudan Cup champions, bags SSP 500,000|publisher=hotinjuba.com|date=14 August 2018}}</ref>
