{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Al-Muhafaza Stadium | nickname = | image = Al-Mohafaza stadium3.jpg | fullname = | location = [[Damascus]], [[Syria]]&nbsp; {{flagicon|Syria}} | latitude = | longitude = | built = | opened = 2011 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Al-Muhafaza SC|Al-Muhafaza]] | operator = Al-Muhafaza | surface = Artificial turf | construction_cost = US $ 2.8 million | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Al-Muhafaza SC|Al-Muhafaza]] | seating_capacity = 1,000 | dimensions = 105 x 67 m }}
'''Al-Muhafaza Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|ملعب المحافظة}}) is a multi-use all-seater [[stadium]] in the [[Syria]]n capital [[Damascus]]. It is mostly used for [[association football|football]] matches and is home to the Syrian Premier League club [[al-Muhafaza SC]]. It also hosts local competitions of [[athletics (sport)|athletics]].
==History== The stadium was opened in 2011 with a capacity of 1,000 seats in the [[Kafr Sousa]] district of Damascus, with a total cost of US$ 2.8 million. It is owned and operated by the Damascus-based [[al-Muhafaza SC|al-Muhafaza]] sports club and is part of a complex that includes an administration building, gymnasium, theatre, restaurants and plazas.<ref name=opening>{{cite news| title=افتتاح مشاريع منشأة نادي "محافظة دمشق| url=http://www.esyria.sy/edamascus/index.php?p=stories&category=news&filename=201304231110011|trans-title=Club previews opening of "Damascus province" facility| date=23 April 2013| publisher=[[Syrian Computer Society]]| accessdate=2015-07-08| language=Arabic}}</ref>
