{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Althawra Sports City Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | image = | caption = | fullname = Althawra Sports City Stadium | location = Al-Thawra Street, [[Sana'a]], [[Yemen]] | coordinates = {{Coord|15|24|43.13|N|44|12|5.65|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | built = | opened = 1986 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Yemen national football team]] | seating_capacity = 30,000 (before bombings) | dimensions = }} '''Altawra Sports City Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|مدينة الثورة الرياضية}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[San‘a’]], [[Yemen]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium holds 30,000 people and was opened in 1986. It is currently the home ground of the [[Yemen national football team]].<ref>[http://www.worldstadiums.com/middle_east/countries/yemen.shtml Infos about Yemeni stadiums (worldstadiums.com)]</ref>
During the [[Saudi Arabian-led intervention in Yemen]] at the [[Yemeni Civil War (2015)|Yemen War]], the stadium was destroyed by a Saudi Arabian's air strike. In 2016, the stadium suffered bomb damage again.<ref>http://yemen.liveuamap.com/en/2016/13-september-althawra-sports-stadium-in-sanaa-was-hit-lastnight/comments</ref>
