{{Infobox union | name = VVCS | country = Netherlands | affiliation = [[Federatie Nederlandse Vakbeweging|FNV]], [[FIFPro]] | members = | full_name = Association of Contract Players | native_name = ''Vereniging van Contractspelers'' | image = Logo vvcs.jpg | founded = 1 January 1961 | current = | head = | dissolved_date = | dissolved_state = | merged_into = | office = [[Hoofddorp]], [[Netherlands]] | people = [[Danny Hesp]] <small>(president)</small> | website = {{URL|http://www.vvcs.nl}} | footnotes = }}
The '''Association of Contract Players''' ({{lang-nl|'''Vereniging van Contractspelers''' — '''VVCS'''}}) is the trade union for professional [[association football|football]] [[football player|player]]s in the [[Netherlands]]. Established on 1 January 1961, it is a member of the [[Dutch Federation of Trade Unions]] and one of the three founding members of [[FIFPro]], whom they share offices with.
Initiatives set up by the association include the VVCS Academy, which help players earn a [[diploma]] during their football careers, and [[Team VVCS]], a team consisting of [[free agent|out-of-contract]] players looking for a new club.
