The '''Croatian Ice Hockey Federation''' ({{lang-hr|Hrvatski savez hokeja na ledu, HSHL}}) is the governing body of ice hockey in [[Croatia]].

The Croatian Ice Hockey Federation was established on November 9, 1935 in [[Zagreb]]. It has been a member of [[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]] since May 7, 1992. It is based in Zagreb, Trg Krešimira Ćosića 11.<ref name="HOO"/>

