The '''Larry Gomes Stadium''', located in [[Malabar, Trinidad and Tobago|Malabar]], [[Arima]], Trinidad and Tobago, is named for [[West Indian cricket team|West Indies cricketer]] [[Larry Gomes]]. The stadium was constructed for the [[2001 FIFA U-17 World Championship|2001 U-17 World Cup]] which was hosted by Trinidad and Tobago. It also hosted games from the [[2010 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]].
