{{WNBA Awards}} The '''WNBA All-Rookie Team''' is an annual [[Women's National Basketball Association]] (WNBA) honor given since the [[2005 WNBA season]] to the top [[rookie]]s during the regular season. Voting is conducted by the [[List of WNBA head coaches|WNBA head coaches]], who are not allowed to vote for players on their own team. Each coach selects five players. A player is given a point for every vote they receive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnba.com/archive/wnba/news/awards08_allrookie.html|title=WNBA.com: Hanns-G Go Beyond 2008 WNBA All-Rookie Team Named|website=www.wnba.com|access-date=2017-02-16}}</ref> The top vote getters comprise the team, regardless of the positions they play. The All-Rookie Team is generally composed of a five-woman lineup, but in the case of a tie at the fifth position the roster is expanded.
[[Candace Parker]] of the [[Los Angeles Sparks]] was named to the All-Rookie Team and won the [[WNBA Most Valuable Player Award]] in the same season. This feat had never before been accomplished.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/wnba/news/story?id=3623772|title=Sparks' Parker wins MVP, rookie of year honors - WNBA - ESPN|date=October 5, 2008|publisher=Sports.espn.go.com}}</ref> In the [[NBA]], only [[Wes Unseld]] has held this distinction.
